Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Pogonatherum paniceum

Assembly is haploid, and the genome is diploid. It has a haploid genome size of 800 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Pogonatherum paniceum from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 2 from the main text, with Pogonatherum paniceum highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Pogonatherum paniceum vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Pogonatherum paniceum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Pogonatherum paniceum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Pogonatherum paniceum

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Pogonatherum paniceum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Pogonatherum paniceum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 lines for each subgenome.
